    "icon": "easter_egg",
    "popupHtml": "<div class=\"p-1\">\n  <div class=\"flex justify-between items-start gap-4 mb-2\">\n    <h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-white leading-tight\">FIB Scientists & Vehicles</h3>\n    <button class=\"copy p-1.5 bg-gray-700/50 hover:bg-blue-500 text-gray-400 hover:text-white rounded transition-colors\" data-clipboard-text=\"-3618.8638123713154, 5114.635247441409\" title=\"Copy Location\">\n      <svg class=\"w-4 h-4\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M8 5H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-1M8 5a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2M8 5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2m0 0h2a2 2 0 012 2v3m2 4H10m0 0l3-3m-3 3l3 3\" /></svg>\n    </button>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3\">In the PS3 & Xbox 360 versions of the game, a pair of scientists and FIB agents can be found here at around 10:00 AM in both story mode and online. Two FIB vehicles spawn next to them, either the FIB Buffalo or the FIB SUV.\n\nModern versions of the game have removed the agents entirely and replaced the FIB vehicles with generic counterparts - but the scientists remain, standing by a satellite roughly pointed in the direction of the spaceship above Fort Zancudo.</p>\n</div>"
